<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>draw in one’s claws • draw in one’s horns</xh5><p> <i>draw in one’s claws</i>—(also: pull in one’s claws) be less hostile and aggressive: They have <u>drawn in their claws</u>, and have become innocent and demure.... The intolerant bigotry of the dark ages is seemingly renounced.</p><p> <i>draw in one’s horns</i>—(also: pull in one’s horns) be less keen or active, and more careful: Nor is there any reason to think that Tyson has learned to <u>draw in his horns</u> where women are concerned.</p> </entry>
